Arts and Culture Minister Nathi Mthethwa has taken to social media to condemn resurgent anti-foreigner sentiment in South Africa. Our African neighbours are our brothers &amp; sisters. We are all Nigerians we are all Zimbabweans we re all South Africans. #WeareAllAfricans. We strongly condemn any attempts to mobilise communities against our fellow African brothers and sisters. This is totally unacceptable. We strongly condemn any attempts to mobilise communities against our fellow African brothers and sisters. This is totally unacceptable.&mdash; Min. Nathi Mthethwa (@NathiMthethwaSA) February 24, 2017